# Contributing

Thanks for taking a look.

This repo is intentionally opinionated.
The goal is not to make the most neutral skill pack possible.
The goal is to make agents more useful for solo founders and very small teams.

## What kinds of contributions are useful

* making the skills clearer without flattening the core philosophy
* improving setup/update safety
* adding realistic examples
* tightening vague language
* reducing false confidence or over-automation
* improving portability without pretending every environment is the same

## What is less useful

* making everything generic
* replacing opinionated rules with vague best practices
* adding complexity before there is a real use case
* turning the skills into enterprise compliance documents

## Style

* prefer plain language
* prefer practical examples
* avoid hype unless the repo actually delivers it
* call out tradeoffs honestly

If you think something is too aggressive, too vague, or too hand-wavy, open an issue.
That is useful feedback here.
